records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT FOR RESTITUTION RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS

Defendant Keith M Jackson-Moore in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Keith M Jackson-Moore in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 195 DAYS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 2, with credit for 135 days time.
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments during term of probation on COUNT 2; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation on COUNT  2; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 195 DAYS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 1, straight time.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 15 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-Restitution set at $22.00 payable to Kimberly K., payable during term of probation.  Restitution to be paid before any Court costs, surcharges and assessments
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected during term of probation;  nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job 
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with Kimberly K. and the address of 6415 W. Wisconsin Avenue and 6323 W. Wisconsin Avenue
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Defendant to appear in Court for his pending case, 14CM4359
-Court has no objection to transfer probation to the State of Indiana 
-Court allows for expungment, if all terms and conditions of probation is successfully completed
Defense motion for modification of bail heard and granted.  Court modifies bail to $100.00 cash TOT Justice Point with the same previous conditions of release.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY to the amended charge in COUNT 1 and the original charge in COUNT 2 and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty on both counts and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.

Part of the global resolution involves the misdemeanor case; court file and state file not in court.  Matter adjourned for sentencing on the felony case and plea and sentencing on the misdemeanor case.
